<br>
Now if it had been a Final Fantasy type sequel (All Final Fantasy sequels have absoltly nothing in common with its predessor (sp?). Each story is seperate and unique and in a different land. All of them except for Final Fantasy X-2, which is an actual sequel to Final Fantasy X. Confused yet? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) I would have bought it.<br>
<br>
Exploring a new land with new monsters, zones, bosses, and dungeons. Thats what made EQ fun when I bought it, exploring the vast lands. But if EQ2 is only 50% new zones, I think I'll pass for the time being.<br>
