<br>
With SCS (Single Character Servers), and a skill tree system, it looks like it will be fairly fuild. <br>
<br>
Plus, since from the looks of it, it will be VERY hard to be a jedi, its not a starting proffession or anything..<br>
<br>
1) Before anything else you have to be &quot;force sensitive&quot; which ANYONE can be, its a diffrent route to get there for everyone, it also may NEVER happen.<br>
2) Once your force sensitive, you have to find a jedi to &quot;train&quot; you.. which is gonna be hard as hell seeing how SWG is set between SW:ANH and SW ESB. All Jedi NPC's in the game are going to be hidden, and NOT being jedi overtly at all for fear of being killed.<br>
3) Once your even a jedi its not easy to A) stay one b) Aviod having 1001 bountys placed on your head by the Empire.<br>
<br>
I'll very much be giving SWG a try. I've been playing EQ for well.. since Oct 10, 1999.<br>
I've seen a lot, done a lot.. but it IS starting to get a little stale lately.. I haven't had as much of an urge to play as of late. And when I have its been more out of loyalty to in game friends, than a want to play.<br>
